Stixbox Function

NOM

    qchisq - The chisquare inverse distribution function

SEQUENCE D'APPEL

x = qchisq(p,d)

PARAMETRES

DESCRIPTION

    The chisquare inverse distribution function

    p probability d degree of freedom (p,d can be scalar or matrix with common size) F for each element of p, F is the value at p of an inverse of the chisquare cumulative distribution function d degrees of freedom
